(42, 5, 20, 43, 2, 25, 25, 'thy sins are forgiven thee', 'Faith and Knowledge of Man', 'This connection highlights the theme of understanding human nature and the role of faith. In Luke, Jesus recognizes the faith of the individuals, while in John, it is noted that Jesus knows what is in man, suggesting a deep awareness of human condition linked to faith.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 20, 51, 3, 13, 13, 'thy sins are forgiven thee', 'Forgiveness in Faith and Action', 'This connection highlights the theme of forgiveness present in both passages. In Luke, forgiveness is granted through faith, while Colossians emphasizes the importance of forgiving others as Christ forgave.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 20, 59, 2, 18, 18, 'thy sins are forgiven thee', 'Faith and Works Connection', 'This connection highlights the relationship between faith and actions. In Luke, faith leads to forgiveness, while James emphasizes that faith is demonstrated through works.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 21, 23, 43, 25, 25, 'Who can forgive sins, but God alone?', 'Forgiveness of Sins', 'This connection highlights the theme of forgiveness, as both passages address the act of forgiving sins. Luke 5:21 emphasizes that only God can forgive sins, while Isaiah 43:25 states that God blots out transgressions.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 21, 41, 2, 6, 7, 'who can forgive sins, but God alone?', 'Blasphemy and Forgiveness of Sins', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of blasphemy and question who has the authority to forgive sins. The scribes and Pharisees in each verse express their reasoning about this authority, highlighting a shared theme of divine prerogative.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 21, 42, 7, 49, 49, NULL, 'Forgiveness of Sins', 'Both passages emphasize the question of who has the authority to forgive sins. The scribes and Pharisees in Luke 5:21 challenge Jesus'' ability to forgive, while those at the meal in Luke 7:49 similarly question his authority to do so.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 21, 19, 32, 5, 5, 'forgive sins, but God alone', 'Forgiveness of Sins Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of forgiveness in both passages. Luke 5:21 questions who can forgive sins, while Psalms 32:5 affirms that the Lord forgives iniquity.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 21, 40, 26, 65, 65, 'who can forgive sins, but God alone', 'Blasphemy Accusations Against Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the accusation of blasphemy against Jesus. In Luke, the scribes question who can forgive sins but God, while in Matthew, the high priest declares Jesus has spoken blasphemy.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 21, 43, 10, 33, 33, 'blasphemies', 'Connection of Blasphemy Accusations', 'Both passages emphasize accusations of blasphemy against Jesus. In Luke, the scribes question who can forgive sins but God alone, while in John, the Jews accuse Jesus of blasphemy for claiming divinity.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 21, 44, 6, 11, 13, 'speaketh blasphemies', 'Blasphemy Accusations in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize accusations of blasphemy against God. In Luke, the scribes question who can forgive sins, while in Acts, false witnesses claim blasphemous words against Moses and God.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 22, 40, 9, 4, 4, 'their thoughts', 'Connection of Jesus Knowing Thoughts', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' ability to perceive thoughts, highlighting his divine insight. The phrases ''perceived their thoughts'' and ''knowing their thoughts'' illustrate this shared theme.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 22, 42, 24, 38, 38, NULL, 'Connection of Troubling Thoughts', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of troubled thoughts arising in the hearts of individuals. Jesus addresses the internal struggles of those around him, highlighting a common human experience.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
