(42, 5, 22, 23, 66, 18, 18, 'thoughts', 'Connection of Thoughts and Works', 'Both passages emphasize the knowledge of thoughts, with Jesus perceiving thoughts in Luke and God knowing works and thoughts in Isaiah. This connection highlights the divine awareness of human inner life.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 22, 40, 12, 25, 25, NULL, 'Connection of Jesus Knowing Thoughts', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' ability to perceive thoughts. In Luke, he asks about reasoning in hearts, while in Matthew, he knows their thoughts and addresses division. This connection highlights his awareness of internal conflicts.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 22, 41, 8, 17, 17, 'reason ye in your hearts', 'Reasoning in Hearts', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of reasoning in the hearts of the listeners. In Luke, Jesus questions their thoughts, while in Mark, he addresses their reasoning about bread, highlighting a lack of understanding.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 22, 44, 5, 3, 3, 'reason ye in your hearts', 'Connection of Heart and Deception', 'This connection highlights the theme of the heart''s intentions. Both passages emphasize the inner thoughts and motivations of individuals, with Jesus perceiving thoughts and Peter addressing Ananias''s deceitful heart.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 23, 40, 9, 5, 5, NULL, 'Connection of Healing and Forgiveness', 'Both passages emphasize the question of what is easier to say regarding forgiveness and healing. The similar phrasing in both verses highlights the relationship between spiritual and physical restoration.', 'parallel', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 23, 41, 2, 9, 9, 'Thy sins be forgiven thee; or to say,', 'Connection of Healing and Forgiveness', 'Both passages emphasize the question of what is easier to say regarding healing and forgiveness. They present a parallel structure in addressing the authority to forgive sins versus the ability to heal physical ailments.', 'parallel', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 24, 23, 53, 11, 11, 'forgive sins', 'Forgiveness and Justification Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of forgiveness and justification in both passages. Luke 5:24 emphasizes the power to forgive sins, while Isaiah 53:11 speaks of justifying many by bearing their iniquities.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 24, 66, 1, 13, 13, 'Son of man', 'Connection of the Son of Man', 'Both passages emphasize the identity of the Son of Man. In Luke, He demonstrates His power to forgive sins, while in Revelation, He is depicted in a glorified state, reinforcing His authority.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 24, 42, 8, 54, 54, 'Arise', 'Connection of Healing Commands', 'Both passages emphasize the command to ''arise'' as a pivotal moment of healing. This connection highlights the authority of Jesus in restoring health and life.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 24, 44, 9, 40, 40, 'Arise', 'Healing and Resurrection Motif', 'Both passages emphasize the command to ''arise'' as a demonstration of divine authority over life and health. This connection highlights the power of Jesus and Peter to restore individuals, showcasing their roles in miraculous healings.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 24, 44, 14, 10, 10, 'Arise, and take up thy couch', 'Healing and Command to Stand', 'Both passages emphasize the act of healing through a command to stand. In Luke, Jesus commands the sick of the palsy to arise, while in Acts, the apostle commands the man to stand upright.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 24, 27, 7, 13, 13, 'Son of man', 'Connection of the Son of Man', 'Both passages emphasize the authority of the ''Son of man.'' In Luke, he demonstrates power to forgive sins, while in Daniel, he is presented before the Ancient of Days, highlighting his significance.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 24, 40, 9, 6, 6, NULL, 'Connection of Healing and Forgiveness', 'Both passages emphasize the authority of the Son of man to forgive sins, demonstrated through the healing of the sick of the palsy. The similar wording in both verses highlights this connection between physical healing and spiritual forgiveness.', 'parallel', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 25, 43, 9, 24, 24, 'glorifying God', 'Praise and Healing Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the act of glorifying God following a miraculous healing. In Luke, the healed man departs ''glorifying God,'' while in John, the blind man is urged to ''Give God the praise.''', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 25, 19, 33, 9, 9, 'glorifying God', 'Divine Authority and Action', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s authoritative command leading to immediate action. In both passages, the act of rising and glorifying God in Luke parallels the idea of God''s word being effective and powerful in Psalms.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 5, 25, 19, 50, 23, 23, 'glorifying God', 'Glorifying God in Praise', 'This connection highlights the act of glorifying God in both passages. In Luke 5:25, the healed man glorifies God, while Psalms 50:23 emphasizes that offering praise glorifies God.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
